Invite the Author 

Invite the Author is an exciting new program bringing Book Groups and
Authors together.

On Monday, February 24, Ann Patchett will phone two reading groups
chosen at random from entries received by January 31. Click here to
enter.
<http://www.harpercollins.com/newsletter/t.asp?ID=197&NL=23&N=227&Subscr
iberID=45656&URL=http://www.harpercollins.com/hc/readers/inviteform.asp>


Next Month: In March, Wally Lamb will discuss his acclaimed New York
Times bestseller I KNOW THIS MUCH IS TRUE
<http://www.harpercollins.com/newsletter/t.asp?ID=197&NL=23&N=227&Subscr
iberID=45656&URL=http://www.harpercollins.com/rd_om/patchettinvitecardco
m/book/0060987561> . Click here to enter.
<http://www.harpercollins.com/newsletter/t.asp?ID=197&NL=23&N=227&Subscr
iberID=45656&URL=http://www.harpercollins.com/hc/readers/inviteform1.asp
> 


Learn more about Invite the Author 

HarperCollins encourages book groups to Invite the Author
<http://www.harpercollins.com/newsletter/t.asp?ID=197&NL=23&N=227&Subscr
iberID=45656&URL=http://www.harpercollins.com/hc/readers/invite.asp>  to
their next meeting. Each month in the Readers' Roundtable
<http://www.harpercollins.com/newsletter/t.asp?ID=197&NL=23&N=227&Subscr
iberID=45656&URL=http://www.harpercollins.com/hc/readers/>
e-newsletter, an author and book selection will be announced. Authors
will participate via telephone with a select number of book groups.

A new author will be announced each month.

Visit the Readers' Roundtable
<http://www.harpercollins.com/newsletter/t.asp?ID=197&NL=23&N=227&Subscr
iberID=45656&URL=http://www.harpercollins.com/hc/readers/>  for more
information, to enter the Invite the Author promotion, and to sign up
for the Readers' Roundtable Newsletter. 

 
<http://www.harpercollins.com/newsletter/t.asp?ID=197&NL=23&N=227&Subscr
iberID=45656&URL=http://www.harpercollins.com>  

